## Change 1: `run_sysid_config.yaml` (new)

```yaml
# Optional config for run_sysid.sh. Usage:
#   ./run_sysid.sh /path/to/this.yaml       (preferred)
#   ./run_sysid.sh /path/to/log.ulg         (old form — uses run_sysid.m defaults)

# The ULG to process. Can also be passed as the 2nd CLI arg to override.
ulg_path: /home/choudhury/logs/log_4_2026-5-13-15-46-26.ulg

# Auto-tune (retune step) knobs — passed to compute_attitude_control_gains.
# These set the target crossover frequencies for pidtune.
wc_inner_Hz:   3.0     # rate-loop target crossover (Hz)
wc_outer_Hz:   1.0     # attitude-loop target crossover (Hz)
PM_target_deg: 60      # phase margin target (deg) for both pidtune calls
```

Any field omitted falls back to the hardcoded default in `run_sysid.m`. The MATLAB side only overrides keys present in the JSON sidecar — so the YAML can be partial.

