## Change 3: `run_sysid.m`

Signature: `function run_sysid(ulg_path, out_dir, config_json_path)` — third arg optional. After the existing `cfg` block (lines 10-22), insert:

```matlab
if nargin >= 3 && ~isempty(config_json_path)
    if ~isfile(config_json_path)
        error('config JSON not found: %s', config_json_path);
    end
    ovr = jsondecode(fileread(config_json_path));
    cfg = apply_overrides(cfg, ovr, {'wc_inner_Hz','wc_outer_Hz','PM_target_deg'});
    fprintf('[run_sysid] cfg overrides: wc_inner=%g wc_outer=%g PM=%g\n', ...
            cfg.wc_inner_Hz, cfg.wc_outer_Hz, cfg.PM_target_deg);
end
```

Helper at the bottom of `run_sysid.m` (helpers section):

```matlab
function cfg = apply_overrides(cfg, ovr, keys)
for k = 1:numel(keys)
    if isfield(ovr, keys{k}) && isnumeric(ovr.(keys{k})) && isfinite(ovr.(keys{k}))
        cfg.(keys{k}) = ovr.(keys{k});
    end
end
end
```

The three target keys are explicitly whitelisted so a typo in the YAML doesn't silently inject something weird into `cfg`.

